com.mparticle.kits

Interface KitIntegration.PushListener

  • Enclosing class:
    KitIntegration

    public static interface KitIntegration.PushListener
    Kits should implement this interface when they have Google Cloud Messaging/push features.

    • Method Detail

      • willHandlePushMessage

        boolean willHandlePushMessage(android.content.Intent intent)
        Kits must implement this method to inspect a push message to determine if it's intended for their SDK. Typically, a given push service will include a predefined key within the payload of a push message that uniquely identifies the push by company.
        Parameters:
        intent - the Intent object from the push-received broadcast
        Returns:
        true if this push should be handled by the given Kit

      • onPushMessageReceived

        void onPushMessageReceived(android.content.Context context,
                           android.content.Intent pushIntent)
        If a Kit returns true from willHandlePushMessage(Intent), this method will be called immediately after. Kits should implement this method to show or otherwise react to a received push message.
        Parameters:
        context -
        pushIntent -

      • onPushRegistration

        boolean onPushRegistration(java.lang.String instanceId,
                           java.lang.String senderId)
        This method will be called when the mParticle SDK successfully registers to receive push messages. This method will be call on app startup and repetitively to aggressively sync tokens as they're updated.
        Parameters:
        instanceId - the device instance ID registered with the GCM scope
        senderId - the senderid with permissions for this instanceId
        Returns:
        true if the push registration was processed.
